  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The advertisement signage, by its inappropriate size, scale, detailed design, and method of illumination, results in an overly dominant, discordant, and visually intrusive form of development that fails to be sensitive to the character of the host building, and fails to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the conservation area, contrary to policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets), LP7 (Advertisements) and PP1 (Public Realm) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020), policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), D8 (Public Realm) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of The London Plan (2021) and Hackney&#x27;s Shopfront Design Guide.&lt;/p&gt;"
